South African rapper Riky Rick will rub shoulders with Milan s fashion A-listers this week.Known for his bold, eclectic style aesthetic, the Durban-born rapper is in theglobal capital of fashion and design for Milan Fashion Week Fall/Winter 2017 which runs from today until February 28.The trip comes after Gucci s creative director and fashion designer, Alessandro Michele, personally invited the local rapper after the public display of his affinity for the brand caught international media attention.As the plane took off yesterday, Riky Rick posted a picture of himself, with a Gucci bag in hand, with the words: From Braamfontein to Milan. Chasing your dream never felt so good. siyabongas@thenewage.co.za